1
00:00:06,139 --> 00:00:07,874
Hey, when I was paying for this today,

2
00:00:08,575 --> 00:00:11,411
the cashier asked
how many spoons I needed,

3
00:00:12,612 --> 00:00:15,181
and without thinking,
I blurted out, "Two, please."

4
00:00:16,082 --> 00:00:18,318
Why can't I just be honest about it, huh?

5
00:00:20,253 --> 00:00:21,888
I mean, I'm fine eating alone.

6
00:00:21,955 --> 00:00:23,123
VANILLA ICE CREAM

7
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:24,457
I may sound like

8
00:00:25,091 --> 00:00:28,461
I'm putting up a strong front,
but I'm really fine.

9
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:31,664
Like, if this were the rest of my life,
I’d be satisfied. Don't you agree?

10
00:00:35,035 --> 00:00:36,036
Right?

11
00:00:39,973 --> 00:00:41,007
It's fine.

12
00:00:41,574 --> 00:00:44,344
I can’t have everything to myself
if I'm not alone…

13
00:00:46,579 --> 00:00:47,814
OUR HAPPY COUPLES STORIES

14
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,015
OUR HAPPY COUPLES STORIES

15
00:00:49,749 --> 00:00:50,850
Are you Mr. Hatano?

16
00:00:50,917 --> 00:00:51,751
Yes.

17
00:00:52,318 --> 00:00:53,953
I’m Momose, and I’ll be assisting you.

18
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:56,189
First, this gentleman here.

19
00:00:56,756 --> 00:00:59,459
He works at the city hall
and is 40 years old.

20
00:00:59,526 --> 00:01:02,262
He’s looking for a partner who enjoys

21
00:01:02,328 --> 00:01:04,297
traveling overseas every year.

22
00:01:05,165 --> 00:01:08,501
And this gentleman is a French chef,
51 years old.

23
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:11,838
He’s a huge music fan, and it seems
both of you have shared interests.

24
00:01:12,338 --> 00:01:14,741
Next is a dancer.

25
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:17,911
He's 39 years old. He loves fishing…

26
00:01:17,977 --> 00:01:19,379
Did something catch your eye?

27
00:01:19,946 --> 00:01:22,982
No, I just happened to notice
how careful you are.

28
00:01:23,049 --> 00:01:24,684
Like with their faces.

29
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:28,621
Details are shown
only after official enrollment.

30
00:01:29,189 --> 00:01:32,959
Rest assured, we take privacy
very seriously.

31
00:01:33,026 --> 00:01:37,063
After all, we’re the industry’s
leading partner agency for gay men.

32
00:01:38,031 --> 00:01:39,032
I see.

33
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:40,667
Would you like to see more?

34
00:01:40,733 --> 00:01:42,735
Maybe tell me your preferences?

35
00:01:42,802 --> 00:01:46,039
For instance, body type.
Do you prefer slim or muscular?

36
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:49,342
What about relationship style?
Wanting to be spoiled or vice versa.

37
00:01:49,409 --> 00:01:50,877
Nothing at all?

38
00:01:53,213 --> 00:01:54,080
Let me think…

39
00:01:58,251 --> 00:02:01,654
- Someone to eat ice cream with.
- Pardon?

40
00:02:01,721 --> 00:02:05,125
You know those giant
family-sized tubs of ice cream?

41
00:02:05,191 --> 00:02:06,426
Oh, that!

42
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:10,296
The kind American kids eat
straight out of while watching movies.

43
00:02:11,064 --> 00:02:12,866
I bought one the other day.

44
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:15,301
But I couldn't finish it.

45
00:02:16,035 --> 00:02:18,605
That's when it hit me.

46
00:02:19,405 --> 00:02:22,308
Wow, I really am alone.

47
00:02:23,776 --> 00:02:25,111
So, if I had to name a preference…

48
00:02:25,178 --> 00:02:28,515
I guess I'd like someone
who’d eat ice cream with me.

49
00:02:28,581 --> 00:02:29,415
That’s sweet.

50
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:31,317
A partner to share a giant ice cream with.

51
00:02:31,384 --> 00:02:33,419
- But…
- But?

52
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:37,557
I don't know. It's starting
to feel ridiculous.

53
00:02:37,624 --> 00:02:40,493
Who would take a middle-aged
gay man's words like that seriously?

54
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,061
Even I think so, hearing myself.

55
00:02:42,128 --> 00:02:43,163
No, not at all!

56
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:44,664
Don’t worry about it.

57
00:02:44,731 --> 00:02:47,834
I’ll keep working away at that ice cream
on my own. Sorry about this.

58
00:02:48,468 --> 00:02:50,370
- Mr. Hatano!
- Y-Yes?

59
00:02:50,436 --> 00:02:54,007
- Love and revolution.
- What?

60
00:02:54,073 --> 00:02:58,478
"Man was born for love and revolution."

61
00:03:01,414 --> 00:03:02,849
It's a quote by Dazai.

62
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,084
Dazai?

63
00:03:05,151 --> 00:03:08,488
Please consider joining us.

64
00:03:09,556 --> 00:03:10,557
NAKAYOSHI PLAZA

65
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,963
TRY FEEDING THE ANIMALS!

66
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:19,966
So cute!

67
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,535
They had a bad reaction to the medicine,

68
00:03:22,602 --> 00:03:24,170
and they threw up twice yesterday.

69
00:03:24,237 --> 00:03:26,639
- Really?
- Once at 1 a.m. and again at 3 a.m.

70
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:27,574
Oh my.

71
00:03:29,509 --> 00:03:30,343
Huh?

72
00:03:31,678 --> 00:03:32,645
What?

73
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:35,215
Oh dear…

74
00:03:40,186 --> 00:03:41,187
Hey there.

75
00:03:42,255 --> 00:03:44,290
Abandoning a cutie like this?

76
00:03:44,357 --> 00:03:47,026
Even Chan and Chasu would get mad,
am I right?

77
00:03:47,093 --> 00:03:48,361
What?

78
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:51,497
At this rate, your apartment is going
to become a zoo, Hatano.

79
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:52,732
- Wait…
- What?

80
00:03:52,799 --> 00:03:55,268
These two were abandoned,
and you took them in, Mr. Hatano?

81
00:03:55,335 --> 00:03:57,337
Yes, and a turtle as well.

82
00:03:57,403 --> 00:03:58,838
Wow.

83
00:03:59,706 --> 00:04:02,208
I can’t really take in any more, though.

84
00:04:02,275 --> 00:04:04,978
My place doesn’t even allow pets.

85
00:04:05,044 --> 00:04:05,945
Really?

86
00:04:06,012 --> 00:04:08,481
Yeah, but it seems to be fine so far.

87
00:04:08,548 --> 00:04:11,150
Hey, maybe we should put up a sign.

88
00:04:11,217 --> 00:04:13,620
"No dumping animals here!"

89
00:04:13,686 --> 00:04:14,654
Right.

90
00:04:14,721 --> 00:04:18,625
Okay, be nice, alright? We’re all going
to be living together now.

91
00:04:19,225 --> 00:04:20,827
Let's all get along, okay?

92
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:23,563
Whoa, that was close.

93
00:04:28,701 --> 00:04:29,702
It's loose here.

94
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:33,773
- Um…
- Yes?

95
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,074
Use this if you'd like.

96
00:04:38,444 --> 00:04:39,912
Thank you.

97
00:04:47,987 --> 00:04:49,689
‪I reserved the cake,

98
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:52,191
reserved the goods,

99
00:04:52,258 --> 00:04:54,827
and reserved the book.

100
00:04:56,429 --> 00:04:57,730
I'm so excited.

101
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:08,541
RESERVATION SLIP

102
00:05:08,608 --> 00:05:11,444
- Sorry about that.
- Oh, no.

103
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:13,246
Thank you.

104
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:17,116
You reserved all of that?

105
00:05:17,917 --> 00:05:19,719
Yes, for books, games,
and stuff like that.

106
00:05:19,786 --> 00:05:22,488
This one here is for a Christmas cake.

107
00:05:22,555 --> 00:05:25,725
Making a reservation is like giving myself
something to look forward to.

108
00:05:25,792 --> 00:05:28,594
I'd then stare at the reservation slips
and smile to myself.

109
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:30,963
Today I placed an order for <i>osechi</i>.

110
00:05:31,531 --> 00:05:32,832
<i>Osechi</i>? Amazing!

111
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:36,002
Sorry for rambling.

112
00:05:36,703 --> 00:05:38,071
No, I'm the one who asked.

113
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,477
You know, that idea of yours
is really nice.

114
00:05:45,111 --> 00:05:47,013
I recommend it.

115
00:05:57,290 --> 00:05:58,991
Can it be fixed?

116
00:05:59,058 --> 00:05:59,892
Yes.

117
00:06:02,061 --> 00:06:05,732
This part was coming loose,
so I'm bracing it with a clamp.

118
00:06:06,499 --> 00:06:07,900
What's that?

119
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:08,968
This.

120
00:06:09,736 --> 00:06:11,003
With this…

121
00:06:12,071 --> 00:06:13,005
There we go.

122
00:06:13,639 --> 00:06:14,474
Solid.

123
00:06:18,745 --> 00:06:21,314
Oh, and this. What should I do about it?

124
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:24,951
You can throw it out.

125
00:06:25,017 --> 00:06:26,452
Alright.

126
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:27,954
Well then.

127
00:06:28,855 --> 00:06:30,189
Thanks again.

128
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,300
HUSBAND-TO-BE: RYOTA YOSHIDA

129
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:43,569
HUSBAND-TO-BE: SAKU SAKUTA

130
00:06:43,636 --> 00:06:44,904
Husband?

131
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:57,283
The guy earlier was probably gay as well,
just like me.

132
00:06:58,985 --> 00:07:00,553
You know, right?

133
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:03,689
We can’t file marriage registration forms.

134
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:04,824
But still…

135
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:07,827
he must’ve wanted to.

136
00:07:07,894 --> 00:07:09,829
‪SAKU SAKUTA

137
00:07:09,896 --> 00:07:10,930
Let's have dinner.

138
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,467
Important?

139
00:07:14,534 --> 00:07:15,368
IMPORTANT

140
00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:19,639
EVICTION NOTICE

141
00:07:19,705 --> 00:07:22,809
"This apartment is strictly no-pets.
Please vacate immediately."

142
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:27,747
Well, guys…

143
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:31,417
looks like we’re moving.

144
00:07:38,024 --> 00:07:38,958
<i>You hear me?</i>

145
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:42,428
<i>You're coming to school today, right?</i>

146
00:07:42,495 --> 00:07:43,863
Yes.

147
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:44,997
<i>I'll be waiting.</i>

148
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:48,534
<i>And about the parent-teacher conference,</i>
<i>can your dad--</i>

149
00:07:49,035 --> 00:07:50,903
He can’t take off work.

150
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:53,773
He said he’ll think about the date.

151
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:56,876
<i>But graduation’s only half a year away.</i>

152
00:07:56,943 --> 00:08:00,480
I'd like to contact your dad myself.
Can you give me his number later?

153
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:04,083
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

154
00:08:05,284 --> 00:08:06,118
Okay.

155
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:07,653
Will do.

156
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:10,790
Also, can you submit
your career sheet today?

157
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:12,291
<i>Yes.</i>

158
00:08:12,358 --> 00:08:13,559
<i>Alright, I’ll be waiti--</i>

159
00:08:19,031 --> 00:08:20,600
- Pets weren't allowed?
- Yeah.

160
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:23,970
What were you thinking?

161
00:08:24,036 --> 00:08:27,206
You should’ve called us sooner.

162
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:29,842
Then we could’ve found something better.

163
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:33,813
I mean, it’s close to work and cheap too.

164
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:36,315
Why don’t you just buy a place?

165
00:08:37,083 --> 00:08:38,150
Huh? Why?

166
00:08:38,217 --> 00:08:39,252
Well,

167
00:08:39,318 --> 00:08:42,121
this time, you got lucky finding one
that fits your circumstances.

168
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:44,657
But who knows if you can keep
renting there forever?

169
00:08:44,724 --> 00:08:47,527
As you get older, renting a new place

170
00:08:47,593 --> 00:08:49,095
becomes much harder.

171
00:08:49,161 --> 00:08:50,229
I know.

172
00:08:50,296 --> 00:08:51,697
Even more so for a loner.

173
00:08:51,764 --> 00:08:53,299
Yeah, yeah.

174
00:08:53,366 --> 00:08:55,301
That's exactly why I'm telling you to buy.

175
00:08:56,002 --> 00:08:58,237
But I don’t have that much money.

176
00:08:58,304 --> 00:09:01,173
That’s what loans are for.

177
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:04,343
Even if I were to take out a loan now,

178
00:09:04,410 --> 00:09:06,045
a 35-year house loan…

179
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:08,981
Is that even possible?

180
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:11,918
- Who knows?
- Oh, come on.

181
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:15,521
It should be here…

182
00:09:16,088 --> 00:09:18,157
- I'll go check.
- Okay.

183
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:22,194
- Welcome! This way.
- Oh.

184
00:09:22,261 --> 00:09:23,095
Got it.

185
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:34,907
Keep going, keep going, keep going.
Okay, stop!

186
00:09:37,209 --> 00:09:39,478
Nice to meet you. Just the other day,

187
00:09:39,545 --> 00:09:41,847
I spoke with you on the phone.

188
00:09:42,848 --> 00:09:45,051
I'm from Hibino Real Estate.
My name is Okabe.

189
00:09:46,485 --> 00:09:49,322
Nice to meet you too.
I’m Inokashira, the landlady.

190
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:52,391
Oh, this is…

191
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:55,061
I'll be in your care from today onward.

192
00:09:55,127 --> 00:09:56,996
I'm Hatano. Nice to meet you.

193
00:09:57,063 --> 00:09:58,030
This way, please.

194
00:09:58,097 --> 00:09:59,665
Thank you.

195
00:09:59,732 --> 00:10:01,400
Let's go. Come on.

196
00:10:01,968 --> 00:10:02,969
Welcome.

197
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:06,339
This place is huge! Awesome!

198
00:10:06,405 --> 00:10:08,374
It's pretty old though.

199
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,508
Oh, no.

200
00:10:09,575 --> 00:10:11,711
It’s far from the station too.

201
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:15,348
Since only one room is occupied,
it’s pretty much an empty house.

202
00:10:15,414 --> 00:10:18,484
But you coming in will liven it up a bit.
This is your unit, Hatano.

203
00:10:18,551 --> 00:10:19,418
Okay.

204
00:10:19,485 --> 00:10:21,854
See? It's a dump, right?

205
00:10:21,921 --> 00:10:24,357
So, don't mind it, pups.

206
00:10:24,423 --> 00:10:26,459
Oh, no. It's cozy.

207
00:10:26,525 --> 00:10:28,027
Really? Then that's great.

208
00:10:28,094 --> 00:10:30,796
So, Ms. Inokashira,
about the contract paperwork…

209
00:10:30,863 --> 00:10:33,432
Oh, yes. Let's go to my room.

210
00:10:33,499 --> 00:10:34,400
Okay.

211
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:35,735
Thank you.

212
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:37,403
It's my pleasure.

213
00:10:38,170 --> 00:10:39,438
Well, guys,

214
00:10:40,106 --> 00:10:43,209
this is our new home.

215
00:10:43,275 --> 00:10:44,110
A round of applause!

216
00:10:52,752 --> 00:10:53,753
<i>Dogs?</i>

217
00:11:01,127 --> 00:11:01,961
Hello.

218
00:11:02,895 --> 00:11:03,729
Hi.

219
00:11:03,796 --> 00:11:05,965
I just moved in. I'm Hatano.

220
00:11:06,032 --> 00:11:08,000
- I'm Kusunoki.
- Nice to meet you.

221
00:11:08,768 --> 00:11:09,835
- Ah.
- What?

222
00:11:10,703 --> 00:11:11,804
Dogs.

223
00:11:13,372 --> 00:11:16,042
- Did they scare you? I'm sorry.
- Oh, no.

224
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:19,912
The dogs are with me.
I hope you don't mind.

225
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:21,047
What are you doing?

226
00:11:21,113 --> 00:11:22,948
Just doing a little rearranging.

227
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:25,851
Um, are your parents around?

228
00:11:25,918 --> 00:11:27,486
- I want to say hel--
- They're not!

229
00:11:27,553 --> 00:11:28,454
Oh, okay.

230
00:11:29,388 --> 00:11:30,322
For now, at least.

231
00:11:31,924 --> 00:11:33,959
Another time then.

232
00:11:45,738 --> 00:11:46,772
Dang it.

233
00:11:50,576 --> 00:11:52,078
Mr. Sakuta.

234
00:11:53,112 --> 00:11:53,946
Kusunoki.

235
00:11:54,780 --> 00:11:55,748
You want to use this?

236
00:11:56,982 --> 00:11:58,050
Thanks.

237
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:01,287
Like I said earlier,

238
00:12:01,353 --> 00:12:03,689
don’t forget
about the parent-teacher meeting.

239
00:12:04,256 --> 00:12:05,257
Okay.

240
00:12:07,293 --> 00:12:09,428
And your career sheet too, later…

241
00:12:11,430 --> 00:12:12,665
I’ll hand it in now.

242
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:15,434
Now?

243
00:12:15,501 --> 00:12:16,368
Got it.

244
00:12:19,271 --> 00:12:20,639
You're heading home already?

245
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:23,476
I just came to turn that in.

246
00:12:24,477 --> 00:12:27,646
